# Btrfs + Snapper One-Click Setup Script
Automated setup script for Btrfs + Snapper on **Arch Linux / CachyOS**.

## Features
- Auto-detect root filesystem and verify it is Btrfs
- Auto-create and mount the standard `.snapshots` subvolume
- Safely configure `/etc/fstab` with backup
- Auto-setup Snapper for `/` (root)
- Enable timeline and cleanup services
- Warning for non-top-level subvolume layouts
- Safe rollback on mount failure

## Usage
```bash
git clone https://github.com/TheChronoClaw/CachyOS-OpenClaw-Podman-one-click-hardening-script.git
cd CachyOS-OpenClaw-Podman-one-click-hardening-script
chmod +x setup-btrfs-snapper.sh
sudo ./setup-btrfs-snapper.sh
